OL,6,FThey all distanced themselves from the
OL,7,Fviolence and disorder in other towns
OL,8,Fand cities, but said they did not feel
OL,9,Fthey were being listened to by the
OL,10,Fmedia or authorities over their
OL,11,Fconcerns about immigration, which they
OL,12,Fclaimed was out of control.
OL,14,FSeveral hundred people turned up
OL,15,Facross the road, at Newgate Street,
OL,16,Ffor an anti-racism and anti-fascist
OL,17,Fprotest.
